snippet.textDisplay:
I'm self-employed.
I pay 32% federal tax rate
I pay 4.65% state tax rate
I pay 7,65% local tax rate for purchase made through my business or personal expenditures.
I pay $3,500 per month for daycare (for two kids) in a mediocre daycare facility.
I have zero credit card debt, small mortgage, zero car payments and I can't afford to buy health insurance for myself for my wife (who is also working full time). Our 3 kids are insured and the premiums are astronomical, so are annual deductibles. How is affordable care act affordable? For whom? I have a choice to buy health insurance for me and my wife or save money for my kids' college. We chose the latter.


I used to be a democrat; however, I can no longer afford to buy benefits for everyone else. Especially because I can't afford to buy it for myself.
I despise Trump, I think he is a horrible human being. However, when I look at the Democrats and what they have to offer (read take away) I think me and my family are going to make a Faustian deal (read deal with the devil).

snippet.textDisplay: Im so GD tired of this!!!! I definitely share Bernie's sentiment regarding healthcare. This is a problem we have had from day one in America. It took all the way until Obama before people finally agreed that people need to have quality healthcare no matter what. Here it is over ten years later and we still don't have it. It's time to stop playing games. No more nit-picking because its only delaying things. Quality healthcare for everyone. Period. The end. Taxes go up a bit? Fine. The top whatever percent pays even more? So be it. Gotta wait a month for a non-emergency? Not a big deal! Hell, the poor wait forever, often until they die, so whatever! Get it done and done NOW. No more games. There are SO many things we pay for (like freaking WALLS) that we could use to pay for it so I really don't care to hear about how we are going to pay for it. Short of our military and food industries, there shouldn't be anything that comes BEFORE paying for the citizens' healthcare! I shouldn't even have to say it but healthy people are happy people. Healthy happy people can work. Healthy happy working people (who are paid right) shop. The whole freaking world runs best when, first, people are healthy. To quote Billie Eilish: "DUH." Just get it done.
